# NPM Authentication Token Configuration
# 
# This file is gitignored and contains your personal npm token for publishing.
# 
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 
# Option 1: Use the setup script (recommended)
#   Run: pnpm run setup:auth
#   This will prompt you for your token and create this file automatically.
#
# Option 2: Manual setup
#   1. Copy this file: cp .npmrc.local.example .npmrc.local
#   2. Get your npm token from: https://www.npmjs.com/settings/YOUR_USERNAME/tokens
#     Or create a new token: npm token create
#   3. Edit .npmrc.local and add your token:
#
# Format:
# //registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=YOUR_NPM_TOKEN_HERE
#
# Example:
# //registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=npm_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Option 3: Use environment variable
#   Set NPM_TOKEN environment variable instead of using this file
#   export NPM_TOKEN=your_token_here
#
# After setup, you can run 'pnpm run pub' without logging in!

